quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
3,101,"How can you disbelieve when you are the ones to whom the signs of Allah are recited and amidst you is His Messenger? Whoever holds fast to Allah will certainly be guided to the straight way."
3,102,"Believers! Fear Allah as He should be feared, and see that you do not die save in the state of submission to Allah. {1}",footnotes:1:They should remain steadfast in their obedience and loyalty to God.
3,103,"Hold fast together to the cable of Allah {1} and be not divided. Remember the blessing that Allah bestowed upon you: you were once enemies then He brought your hearts together, so that through His blessing you became brothers. You stood on the brink of a pit of fire and He delivered you from it. {2} Thus Allah makes His signs clear to you that you may be guided to the right way. {3}",footnotes:1:The expression 'cable of Allah'
3,104,"And from among you there must be a party who invite people to all that is good and enjoin the doing of all that is right and forbid the doing of all that is wrong. It is they who will attain true success."
3,105,"Do not be like those who fell into factions and differed among themselves {1} after clear signs had come to them. A mighty chastisement awaits them.",footnotes:1:The reference is to those communities which received clear and straightforward teachings of the true religion but who had abandoned the fundamentals
3,106,"On the Day when some faces will turn bright and ther faces will turn dark. Those whose faces have turned dark will be told: 'Did you fall into unbelief after you had been blessed with belief? Taste, then, chastisement for your unbelief."
3,107,"And those whose faces have turned bright, they will be in the mercy of Allah, and therein they shall abide."
3,108,"These are the mes sages of Allah which We recite to you in truth, and Allah desires no wrong {1} to the people of the world.",footnotes:1:Since God does not want to subject people to any wrong He illuminates the straight path of their salvation
